The Redeemed Christian Church of God Prince of Peace Mega Parish, Lagos Province 26, has embarked on monthly community social responsibility (CSR) to the Ilasamaja church community, Lagos. The host, Pastor Babatunde Timothy Akinyeye, Pastor Seun Adesina and Pastor Omolola Akoto, informed that the parish gave out free foodstuff, cooked foods on a monthly basis to cushion the effect of the financial hardship in Nigeria.” Akinyeye said, “We give out free rice, yam, beans, plantain, assorted drinks, bottle water, indomie noodles, spaghetti, bread, salt, maggi and source among others.” Adeboye Mark’s 80th Birthday With Donation Of Dialysis… We Need Impactful Leadership In Nigeria – James Other programme are teen and youth vigils meant to set the tune for the year 2022 with God in the youth of the church.